<h2>Part 1: SmealConnect
</h2>
<p>This week, we'll get you set up in SmealConnect. SmealConnect is a password-protected career opportunities and networking website designed to connect Penn State Smeal College of Business students and alumni to corporate recruiters. The system is primarily utilized to post internship opportunities for undergraduate students, internship and full-time opportunities for MBAs, and experienced-hire positions for Smeal alumni. Additionally, added features allow on-campus support and coordination for employer interviewing. Click the link below to view the video walkthrough of how to get started with SmealConnect.
</p>
<p>Link: <a href="https://media.smeal.psu.edu/content_student/undergrad/careers/smealconnect_screencast/smealconnect_screencast.mp4" target="_blank">SmealConnect Webshop (opens in new window)</a>
</p>
<p>Create your SmealConnect Account if you did not request it last week as directed. Visit <a href="http://careerconnections.smeal.psu.edu/internships-co-ops/smeal-connect/">http://careerconnections.smeal.psu.edu/internships-co-ops/smeal-connect/</a> and scroll to "Accessing the System" for the instructions. It takes 1-2 business days for accounts to be activated.
</p>
<p>Once your account has been created and activated, log in and fill out your profile. This is worth credit for class. I will receive a report of students from our class who are active in SmealConnect.&nbsp;
</p>
<p><strong>Knowledge Check </strong>
</p>
<p>[ciscode|rev=1|tool=elmsmedia|item=55|entity_type=node]
