<h2>Part 2: Preparing Your Resume
</h2>
<p>Now that you have created your SmealConnect profile, we will look toward preparing your resume to attend career events here at Smeal. To get started, please review the following video about resume basics from the Smeal Career and Corporate Connections office.
</p>
<p>Link: <a href="https://meeting.psu.edu/p1m4tjechc8/?launcher=false&amp;fcsContent=true&amp;pbMode=normal" target="_blank">Resume Webshop from Career and Corporate Connections</a> (opens in a new window)
</p>
<p>After watching the webshop, review the following examples of resumes (there are two pages of examples included in the website below). You may choose to view the resume of the major you intend to pursue, or choose a major that you think you might be interested in to get a sense of the type of work those majors typically do.&nbsp;
</p>
<p>Example Resumes by Major: <a href="http://careerconnections.smeal.psu.edu/resources/?ctag%5B%5D=resume-writing-and-sample-resumes">http://careerconnections.smeal.psu.edu/resources/?ctag%5B%5D=resume-writing-and-sample-resumes</a>
</p>
<p><strong>Question</strong>
</p>
<p>[ciscode|rev=1|tool=elmsmedia|item=54|entity_type=node]
</p>
<h3>Assignment
</h3>
<p>Create a draft resume and add it as an attachment to a post in the appropriate Canvas discussion forum. You may also wish to bring a printed copy to class if you like. We will be trading resumes and editing them as well as offering suggestions for improvement together in class. After we're done with our workshop, you will make your edits and submit your second versions to VMock.
</p>
